node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
.DS_Store
.env
.env.local
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Generated runtime files
projects/*/logs/*
!projects/*/logs/.gitkeep
projects/*/output/*
!projects/*/output/.gitkeep
projects/*/qa/*
!projects/*/qa/.gitkeep

# proof_approval.json is the one human-authored approval record -- see
# schemas/proof_approval.schema.json. orvyq-final-encode.yml reads it from
# the committed repo (not a workflow artifact), so it must be committed by
# an explicit human action.
#
# frozen_candidate.json is deliberately NOT carved out here anymore: it is
# always-regenerate build output, produced fresh by orvyq-review.yml on
# every run and shipped only inside that run's render bundle artifact (see
# docs/canonical-candidate-audit.md) -- committing it back to the branch was
# what entangled candidate identity with an unrelated bot commit's SHA.
# Historical frozen_candidate.json files already committed before this fix
# remain tracked (this rule only affects untracked/new changes) and stay in
# place as historical reference, per the task's own "do not delete history"
# rule.
!projects/*/qa/proof_approval.json

# Always-regenerate build output -- see docs/golden-renderer-map.md section 5.
# Never hand-commit this; if it must be inspected, add a CI check that it is
# byte-identical to a fresh `build-project` run instead.
projects/*/remotion/render_ready_project/
projects/*/direction/edit_plan.json
projects/*/remotion/scene_config.json
projects/*/remotion/asset_map.json
projects/*/remotion/captions.json

# Binary project assets are not committed to this repo. .gitattributes
# configures Git LFS tracking for when they are (footage *.mp4 + provenance,
# assets/audio/final_voice.mp3), matching the golden repo's own convention of
# committing one-time-curated footage/narration but fetching evidence/music/
# SFX fresh per build -- but this session's egress policy blocks the LFS
# object-verify callback, which goes directly to lfs.github.com regardless of
# the session's own repo-scoped git proxy (confirmed via
# /root/.ccr/__agentproxy/status: "403 to CONNECT ... policy denial", the
# same non-retriable class documented in /root/.ccr/README.md), so no LFS
# push is possible from here even though the upload itself succeeds.
# docs/source-audit.md section 4 and the Phase 5 report explain the existing
# workaround this project already relies on for the motion hook's footage:
# .github/workflows/*.yml recover real footage/narration from the golden
# repo directly during the CI run, which has unrestricted network access.
# scripts/orvyq_materialize_footage.mjs + projects/*/migration/
# external_assets.json extend that same recovery mechanism to the full
# 25-clip contextual footage set this project now uses in both modes. A
# future session with working LFS push can commit these assets properly and
# remove this ignore rule.
projects/*/assets/
